00:33:30.920 --> 00:33:32.560 align:middle line:90%
especially.

00:33:32.560 --> 00:33:34.530 align:middle line:84%
The foundation and
the fundamentals

00:33:34.530 --> 00:33:39.090 align:middle line:84%
of this information
I put into the book

00:33:39.090 --> 00:33:41.610 align:middle line:84%
called UBUNTU
Contributionism," which

00:33:41.610 --> 00:33:44.930 align:middle line:84%
was subtitled "A Blueprint
for Human Prosperity."

00:33:44.930 --> 00:33:48.610 align:middle line:10%
And to my surprise,
this book has now

00:33:48.610 --> 00:33:52.660 align:middle line:10%
been translated into
a number of languages.

00:33:52.660 --> 00:33:57.560 align:middle line:10%
Spanish, French, and Zulu are
in translation at the moment,

00:33:57.560 --> 00:34:01.480 align:middle line:10%
and more languages are
coming-- Chinese, and Russian,

00:34:01.480 --> 00:34:06.850 align:middle line:10%
and who knows what-- I
forget the other languages.

00:34:06.850 --> 00:34:09.219 align:middle line:84%
So it's completely
out of control.

00:34:09.219 --> 00:34:12.690 align:middle line:84%
I certainly did not set
out to start a movement.

00:34:12.690 --> 00:34:15.870 align:middle line:84%
So if you think I'm sitting here
because I've planned this, no.

00:34:15.870 --> 00:34:17.389 align:middle line:84%
I have no idea why
I'm sitting here,

00:34:17.389 --> 00:34:19.030 align:middle line:90%
why I'm sharing this with you.

00:34:19.030 --> 00:34:20.739 align:middle line:90%
Somehow it just happened.

00:34:20.739 --> 00:34:24.600 align:middle line:84%
I just realized that we don't
need money a long time ago,

00:34:24.600 --> 00:34:27.606 align:middle line:84%
and I started talking about
a world without money in 2005

00:34:27.606 --> 00:34:29.955 align:middle line:84%
while I was writing
"Slow Species of God"

00:34:29.955 --> 00:34:31.580 align:middle line:84%
when I suddenly
realized in my research

00:34:31.580 --> 00:34:33.699 align:middle line:84%
into origins of human
kind-- I realize

00:34:33.699 --> 00:34:36.060 align:middle line:84%
that we lived without
money for much longer

00:34:36.060 --> 00:34:37.551 align:middle line:90%
than we've lived with money.

00:34:37.551 --> 00:34:39.300 align:middle line:84%
So that's what when I
started saying, wow,

00:34:39.300 --> 00:34:40.687 align:middle line:90%
how is that possible?

00:34:40.687 --> 00:34:42.520 align:middle line:84%
Because everybody thinks,
oh, we need money.

00:34:42.520 --> 00:34:43.949 align:middle line:84%
Without money, how are
we going to survive?

00:34:43.949 --> 00:34:45.199 align:middle line:90%
How are we going to buy stuff?

00:34:45.199 --> 00:34:47.730 align:middle line:90%


00:34:47.730 --> 00:34:51.630 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it's that
knee jerk reaction,

00:34:51.630 --> 00:34:53.440 align:middle line:84%
and I realized that
for thousands of years

00:34:53.440 --> 00:34:55.980 align:middle line:84%
people lived very happily,
and they lived well,

00:34:55.980 --> 00:34:57.150 align:middle line:90%
and they were knowledgeable.

00:34:57.150 --> 00:34:59.820 align:middle line:84%
They could do things, and they
built incredible structures

00:34:59.820 --> 00:35:03.120 align:middle line:84%
like the pyramids and
ancient structures,

00:35:03.120 --> 00:35:06.170 align:middle line:84%
and they did all
this without money.

00:35:06.170 --> 00:35:09.280 align:middle line:84%
And so I started thinking
about what would it

00:35:09.280 --> 00:35:12.660 align:middle line:84%
be if we removed
money from the system?

00:35:12.660 --> 00:35:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And slowly but surely
it started evolving,

00:35:14.980 --> 00:35:18.500 align:middle line:84%
and the more solutions I
found for the basic questions,

00:35:18.500 --> 00:35:22.200 align:middle line:84%
the easier it became to answer
more complicated questions.

00:35:22.200 --> 00:35:24.680 align:middle line:84%
How is this going to work
in a world without money?

00:35:24.680 --> 00:35:28.690 align:middle line:84%
And I'll tell you, within the
first three to six months,

00:35:28.690 --> 00:35:31.050 align:middle line:84%
it became like a
drug where I couldn't

00:35:31.050 --> 00:35:32.250 align:middle line:90%
stop thinking about it.

